    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-11T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-11T19:00:00-05:00" n="868"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d868">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.1051/612a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-11T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 11, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Please confer immediately with the Commander of the Guardia and report in
                    detail by first possible air mail the plans for carrying out the policy as set
                    forth in the memorandum of February 5, 1931,<note n="49" xml:id="d868fn49">
                        <ref target="frus1931v02#pg_841">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 841</ref>.</note> in so far as it
                    relates to turning over the Guardia Nacional to Nicaraguan control.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
